  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An extensive uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted covering inlet velocity, fluid viscosity, and impeller clearance tolerances; the UQ results informed the validation comparisons and confirmed that the relative hemolysis index predictions are robust across the design space. Sensitivity rankings from the UQ campaign are summarised in the ValidationResult narratives below.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
